Moderator: Anyone who passes a training receives this role Administrator: Good conduct as a moderator, expresses interest in being promoted, wishes to handle issues brought up by moderators and premoderators. Has permissions in group to change user ranks, allowing for the promotion of group members. Head Administrator: Leads the rest of the staff team, handles administrative level functions in the group, such as accepting members, managing ranks and other to be determined responsibilities. Department System (possible, not 100% confirmed): Staff Team will be organised into Departments which will have responsibility over certain duties as well as patrolling the game and enforcing rules. Departments could include: Admissions: Compiling a list of people not to be allowed in the group, and declining those people whenever accepting group join requests. Education: In charge of hosting Mod Trainings. Anyone in this department would have to be taught how to host such a training by Haru. Player Support: Handles Ban Appeals. Partnership: Actively searches for partners for the group. If you have ideas for departments or the staff team as a whole, feel free to DM me. Departments will be lead by a Head Administrator, who will be the "Department Chief". An Assistant Department Chief will be selected by the Department Chief and will be an Administrator. Not all Administrators will be assistants, not all Head Administrators will be Chiefs, these are simply the required ranks for these roles. All group members are being demoted to Premoderator. Those who passed trainings will be Moderator. Do not hesitate to ping or DM me to ask to be trained. More information + quotas for staff will be introduced later.

@Staff Member Hello everyone, since Administrator elections were cancelled a while back, the Administrator team has stayed the exact same for quite some time. This is not the way I would like it to be, as I think it would be useful to provide all staff members with some sort of goal to strive for. Below is the new method by which Administrators and Head Administrators will be chosen from now on. Every four weeks, the process for choosing the new Administrators/Head Administrators will begin. This is a three day long process.
  • On day one, a new Head Admin will be chosen based on which member of the previous Administrator team was the most productive.
  • On day two, Administrator applications will be opened & all staff members will be able to apply by filling out the forum and sending it in my DM's.
  • On day three, the applications will close and the Staff Council will open. This council comprises of the two Staff Managers (me and Lokbro), and the new Head Administrator. The council will read through all of the applications, and each member will vote on which of the applicants are best suited to become Administrators. By the end of day three, the new Administrators will be chosen and the process will repeat.
The next Head Admin will be chosen on 4/28/23, and Admin Apps will open on 4/29/23. If you have any questions about this process, please go ahead and ask me.

@Staff Member Hello everyone, since Administrator elections were cancelled a while back, the Administrator team has stayed the exact same for quite some time. This is not the way I would like it to be, as I think it would be useful to provide all staff members with some sort of goal to strive for. Below is the new method by which Administrators and Head Administrators will be chosen from now on. Every four weeks, the process for choosing the new Administrators/Head Administrators will begin. This is a three day long process.
  • On day one, a new Head Admin will be chosen based on which member of the previous Administrator team was the most productive.
  • On day two, Administrator applications will be opened & all staff members will be able to apply by filling out the forum and sending it in my DM's.
  • On day three, the applications will close and the Staff Council will open. This council comprises of the two Staff Managers (me and Lokbro), and the new Head Administrator. The council will read through all of the applications, and each member will vote on which of the applicants are best suited to become Administrators. By the end of day three, the new Administrators will be chosen and the process will repeat.
The next Head Admin will be chosen on 4/28/23, and Admin Apps will open on 4/29/23. If you have any questions about this process, please go ahead and ask me.
